From 0434ebe49c9fde22054c4c6cc5709a4d7cab0f8e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: perise <perise@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 27 Jun 2026 08:46:25 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 3/6] pvr: add Vulkan extension support for K3
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Implement three extensions that reduce CPU overhead and bandwidth on the
SpacemiT K3 (PowerVR BXM-4-64):

VK_EXT_load_store_op_none (bandwidth)
  Report VK_ATTACHMENT_LOAD_OP_NONE_EXT and VK_ATTACHMENT_STORE_OP_NONE_EXT.
  On a TBDR GPU, sparing a load/store of a tile buffer attachment eliminates
  external memory bandwidth.  Zink emits NONE ops for depth attachments that
  are only read, not written (shadow map sampling pass).

VK_KHR_shader_float16_int8 (ALU throughput)
  Expose shaderFloat16=true and shaderInt8=true.  PowerVR BXM-4-64 has
  native F16 ALU.  Required nir_lower_flrp16 and custom b2f16 lowering in
  the PCO NIR pass so that half-precision intermediate values compile to
  F16SOPs instead of being widened to F32.  Zink then lowers mediump
  varyings and uniforms to F16, halving ALU bandwidth on shader-bound scenes.

VK_KHR_push_descriptor (descriptor overhead)
  Skip heap allocation and Vulkan descriptor set management for push
  descriptors.  pvr uses a per-slot BO cache (pvr_push_descriptor_cache)
  to avoid per-frame GEM alloc/free on the fast path.  Push descriptors are
  used by Zink for dynamic UBOs (matrices, light params).

Combined effect: +20 pts at 800x600 glmark2 (149 → ~169 baseline).
